description: ----------------- Group Description -----------------  ** At registration, please be sure to *include your CALLSIGN and indicate if you are a current member of WSARC.*  The West Seattle Amateur Radio Club is your best-bet for social contact or technical assistance from the local hams in West Seattle. The club has a rich history stretching back to the 1930's. We offer weekly radio nets on three club repeaters using the club call of W7AW and monthly breakfasts and club meetings in West Seattle.  We host a monthly club meeting on the third Saturday of each month, from 9:30-11:00ish at the Salvation Army Community Center, in White Center. And, a monthly Elmers' Breakfast Gathering & Help Session, every 1st Saturday from 8:00-9:30 am, at the Great American Diner & Bar.  The club offers licensing classes to become a ham radio operator. Classes and exams are available for anyone interested in joining our community. If you live or operate in the West Seattle area, or can get to West Seattle
